    <title>1830 Jun. 29, Carthage [Tennessee] [to] Louisa C. Hazard / A. Fergusson</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter from Adam Fergusson to his sister-in-law Louisa C. Hazard, dated June 29, 1830. Fergusson writes of an address to the students at Locust Grove Female Academy by the Honorable Felix Grundy, Esq. Grundy hopes to involve the ladies in the Temperance movement. Fergusson feels that their voices are very respected and that their involvement will be beneficial.</abstract>
